			<ns0:name>k...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112873510090665368075/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">force_align_arg_pointer is only supported in IA32 mode, not in x86-64 mode. And I think that Andrey's code was quite ready to work with unaligned stack - IRT crashed, not user's code if he's diagnosis is correct.

It also crashed when presented with NULL TLS pointer if I remember correctly. Both possibilities are usually impossible when newlib or glibc are used, but may be problematic if language uses it's own runtime (for example Go).</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-09-06T19:07:46.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-09-06T19:07:46.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 5 by k...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2232#c5" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2232/comments/full/5" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>